ut-agentlog` normalizes to the stored key:\n\n```text\ngitbutler-review:13936\n```\n\nThis review target is optional because captured metadata may not always include\nreview information. When it is present, it is the strongest first lookup for a\nPR-scoped Agent Trail.\n\nThe server can also use the GitHub API to resolve PR metadata, especially the\nhead branch behind the pull request. For the URL above, th\n[TRUNCATED]\nhere are no major architecture blockers left. Before building, the remaining\nquestions are implementation-shaping decisions:\n\n1. **PR-to-agentlog lookup merge.** Search both MVP targets: the PR/review key\n   and the PR head branch. Review matches rank above branch-only matches. Still\n   decide the exact dedupe/merge behavior for sessions that match both.\n2. **Fork PR behavior.** Decide what happens for PRs from forks. The metadata\n   may live on the base repository, the fork, both, or neither.\n3. **Snapshot identity.** Define what makes a snapshot unique: PR number,\n   metadata ref OID, selected session/turn keys, source commit SHA, generation\n   time, or some combination.\n4. **Refresh and invalidation.** Decide when a cached snapshot is reused versus\n   rebuilt after a metadata re-fetch.\n5. **Projection payload.** Define the JSON shape Forge gets from\n   `but-agentlog`: overview facts, sessions, turns, grouped records, relevance\n   evidence, warnings, and exact drill-down handles.\n6. **Public redaction bar.** Decide the stricter public-web redaction rules on\n   top of local agentlog redaction: paths, command output, environment snippets,\n   usernames, URLs, tokens, and tool payloads.\n7. **Weak/no-data states.** Write exact product behavior for: metadata ref not\n   found, metadata found but no agentlog keys, related sessions found but weak\n   relevance, and redaction/projection failure.\n8. **Initial UI wireframe.** Pick the first screen layout before coding:\n    header, PR context, overview, session list, selected turn timeline, grouped\n    record drawer, raw evidence drawer.\n\nThe canonical PR target key is now decided for v1: PR number as a\n`but-agentlog` review target, normalized to `gitbutler-review:<number>`.\n\nThe metadata ref path is also decided for v1: fetch `refs/meta/main` from the\npublic repository resolved from the PR URL.\n\nThe most important remaining decisions are snapshot identity, projection\npayload, and the public redaction bar.\n\n## Implementation Boundary\n\nKeep the primitive crate boring.\n\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T14:38:51.424Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}